IMPLEMENTATION APPROACH:
Use esbuild's `define` option in sidekick-dist/package.json bundle script to inject version at build time:

```javascript
// In sidekick-dist bundle script
const pkg = require('./package.json');
esbuild.build({
  define: {
    'process.env.SIDEKICK_VERSION': JSON.stringify(pkg.version)
  },
  // ...
})
```

Then in CLI arg handling:
```typescript
if (args.version || args.v) {
  console.log(process.env.SIDEKICK_VERSION);
  process.exit(0);
}
```

Single source of truth: sidekick-dist/package.json. No sync headaches.

description:
When a placeholder like {personaName} is empty (no personas, disabled persona), the surrounding decoration text (brackets, pipes) still appears, resulting in '[] | opus-4' instead of 'opus-4'.

Proposed solution: Allow placeholders to specify prefix/suffix that only render when the value is non-empty.

Syntax options:
1. {personaName,prefix='[',suffix='] | '}
2. Conditional blocks: {#if personaName}[{personaName}] | {/if}
3. Optional wrapper: {?[personaName] | ?}

Discovered during persona acceptance testing (test #9).
